\section{Filter coverage (v0.1)}{

The Commissie m.e.r. portal's taxonomy values (theme, advice type, status)
are driven by a JavaScript FacetWP layer that does not yield to programmatic
access without a browser session. As a result, this version applies only
the filters that are extractable from each detail page:
\itemize{
\item \code{query} — case-insensitive substring match against the title and URL slug
\item \code{date_range} — matches against \code{date_decision} (the "Laatste advies
uitgebracht op" field)
\item \code{province} — substring match against \code{competent_authority}
(e.g. \code{province = "Groningen"} matches "Provincie Groningen")
}

The arguments \code{theme}, \code{advice_type}, and \code{status} are accepted (and
validated against the vocabularies in \code{\link[=get_assessments_coverage]{get_assessments_coverage()}}) but
currently emit a one-shot warning when supplied. A future release will wire
